#Text=The PARALLEL optimizer hint is used to force parallel scanning.The NO_PARALLEL optimizer
#Text=hint prevents usage of a parallel scan.
#Text=Parallel scanning allows multiple background workers to simultaneously scan a table
#Text=Compared with other methods such as a sequential scan, this
#Text=The table in which a parallel hint is used.
#Text=The value of the parallel_degree parameter is a positive integer that specifies the
#Text=desired number of workers to be used in a parallel scan.
#Text=the smaller value between this parameter and the configuration parameter max_parallel_workers_per_gather
#Text=is used as the planned number of workers.
#Text=If DEFAULT is set, the maximum possible parallel degree is used.
#Text=If both parallel_degree and DEFAULT are omitted, the query optimizer determines the
#Text=In this case, if the table parameter has been set with the parallel_workers
#Text=storage parameter, the value of parallel_workers is used as the parallel degree.
#Text=the optimizer uses the maximum possible parallel degree specified by DEFAULT.
#Text=more information about the parallel_workers storage parameter, visit parallel_workers.
#Text=Regardless of the circumstance, the parallel degree never exceeds the value of max_parallel_workers_per_gather.
#Text=The following configuration parameter settings are valid:SHOW max_worker_processes;
#Text=(1 row)The following example shows the default scan on the pgbench_accounts table.
#Text=scan is shown in the query plan.
#Text=(1 row)The following example uses the PARALLEL hint.
#Text=In the query plan, the Gather node that
#Text=launches the background workers specifies that two workers are planned to be used.
#Text=Note If trace_hints is set to on, the INFO: [HINTS] lines are displayed to indicate that
#Text=PARALLEL has been supported by pgbench_accounts and other hints.
#Text=These examples show the same output, where
#Text=[HINTS] SeqScan of [pgbench_accounts] rejected due to PARALLEL hint.
#Text=(3 rows)The following example shows an increased value of max_parallel_workers_per_gather:SET max_parallel_workers_per_gather TO 6;
#Text=(1 row)The same query on pgbench_accounts is used again with no specified parallel degree
#Text=The number of planned workers has been determined by the optimizer
#Text=(3 rows)A value of 6 is specified for the parallel degree parameter of the PARALLEL hint.
#Text=The value is returned as the planned number of workers in the following example:
#Text=(3 rows)The same query is used with the DEFAULT setting for the parallel degree.
#Text=indicate that the maximum allowable number of workers is planned.
#Text=Note This format in which the ALTER TABLE statement sets the parallel_workers parameter
#Text=The parallel_workers parameter is set by the PSQL \\d+ statement.ALTER TABLE pgbench_accounts SET (parallel_workers=3);
#Text=Options: fillfactor=100, parallel_workers=3If the PARALLEL hint is provided with no parallel degree, the returned number of planned
#Text=workers is the value of the parallel_workers parameter.
#Text=(3 rows)The parallel degree value or DEFAULT in the PARALLEL hint overwrites the parallel_workers
#Text=The following example shows the NO_PARALLEL hint.
